01:00:43,993 --> 01:00:46,427
- It's not a problem.
- I don't know why I just did that.

811
01:00:46,529 --> 01:00:47,757
- Don't apologize.
- Are you sure?

812
01:00:47,864 --> 01:00:50,424
Yes. Shit, this is my stop.

813
01:00:50,533 --> 01:00:52,933
- You're getting off here?
- Yeah, I've gotta get off.

814
01:00:53,035 --> 01:00:55,731
But, really, don't worry about it.

815
01:00:56,439 --> 01:00:59,602
I don't know,
it's just 'cause we've been drinking, and...

816
01:00:59,709 --> 01:01:02,200
It's just we're on a team, we work together.

817
01:01:02,311 --> 01:01:04,745
- I get it.
- Just don't feel bad about this.

818
01:01:04,847 --> 01:01:07,372
Okay. Sure. Bye.

819
01:01:27,502 --> 01:01:31,233
<i>My world was flashing by
at a million miles a minute.</i>

820
01:01:32,574 --> 01:01:35,543
<i>I had saved over $100,000.</i>

821
01:01:36,711 --> 01:01:38,770
<i>Only $200,000 to go.</i>

822
01:01:39,981 --> 01:01:43,917
<i>But there was still one thing
I couldn't get off my mind.</i>

823
01:01:54,329 --> 01:01:56,024
<i>The moment we left campus,</i>

824
01:01:56,131 --> 01:01:58,395
<i>the concept of vectors and formulas</i>

825
01:01:58,500 --> 01:02:01,196
<i>were replaced with counting,
shuffle tracking</i>

826
01:02:01,303 --> 01:02:04,466
<i>knowing when to hit
and knowing when to color out.</i>

827
01:02:04,706 --> 01:02:07,300
<i>I was becoming a pro on all levels.</i>

828
01:02:07,776 --> 01:02:09,573
<i>I made more money in one trip to Vegas</i>

829
01:02:09,678 --> 01:02:15,082
<i>than I would have in 5 years, 9 months,
12 days and 6 hours at J. Press Menswear.</i>

830
01:02:17,452 --> 01:02:19,920
<i>In Boston, I was just Ben Campbell.</i>

831
01:02:20,956 --> 01:02:24,687
<i>But in Vegas, I could be anyone I wanted.</i>

832
01:02:24,793 --> 01:02:27,091
You know what I'm gonna do?
You know what I'm gonna do?

833
01:02:27,195 --> 01:02:30,460
I'm gonna throw a half-mill down
on the one hand. Come on. Hit me!

834
01:02:30,565 --> 01:02:33,795
<i>One night, I'd be the high-rolling heir
to a pharmaceutical fortune.</i>

835
01:02:33,901 --> 01:02:37,029
Leon, could you make sure
there's some champagne,

836
01:02:37,438 --> 01:02:41,101
maybe some strawberries
waiting in there for me.

837
01:02:41,609 --> 01:02:42,940
I may not be alone.

838
01:02:43,043 --> 01:02:46,672
<i>The next, I'd be the hottest video game
designer on the West Coast.</i>

839
01:02:47,281 --> 01:02:48,680
There it is.

840
01:02:48,782 --> 01:02:52,274
Winner, winner, chicken dinner!

841
01:02:56,357 --> 01:02:58,518
No, please, keep going.
This video's priceless.

842
01:03:00,027 --> 01:03:01,654
<i>I'm not gonna lie.</i>

843
01:03:02,363 --> 01:03:06,857
<i>It did get, well, a little confusing sometimes.</i>

844
01:03:07,801 --> 01:03:09,393
<i>Operator, how can I help you?</i>

845
01:03:09,503 --> 01:03:11,801
Yeah, room service.

846
01:03:11,905 --> 01:03:14,339
<i>Excuse me?
Honey, we don't do room service.</i>

847
01:03:14,441 --> 01:03:16,102
What do you mean,
you don't do room service?

848
01:03:16,210 --> 01:03:18,576
<i>I mean, we don't do room service.</i>

849
01:03:30,624 --> 01:03:33,286
<i>In Boston, we had a secret.</i>

850
01:03:39,066 --> 01:03:42,159
<i>In Vegas, we had a life.</i>

851
01:03:50,643 --> 01:03:55,080
<i>Micky said I was gonna have more fun
than I could possibly imagine.</i>

852
01:03:56,249 --> 01:03:57,807
<i>And he was right.</i>

853
01:04:01,788 --> 01:04:03,847
- Hey, Jamie. There you go.
- Nice.

854
01:04:03,956 --> 01:04:05,651
<i>It was too good to be true.</i>

855
01:04:05,758 --> 01:04:09,785
There you go. All right,
my night just got better. Thank you, Joe.

856
01:04:10,863 --> 01:04:13,730
<i>And it felt like it was never going to end.</i>

857
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:27,204
Clark? I think I got something over here.

858
01:04:27,914 --> 01:04:29,609
Take a look at this.

859
01:04:32,118 --> 01:04:34,586
That guy? He's a kid.

860
01:04:34,687 --> 01:04:38,418
He was on the tape from last week.
Got a big roll and he's crushing your table.

861
01:04:38,524 --> 01:04:40,890
Plus, he ordered a tonic and lime.

862
01:04:40,993 --> 01:04:43,689
Tonic and lime. What does that mean?

863
01:04:43,796 --> 01:04:46,026
It means he wants you
to think he's drinking.

864
01:04:46,132 --> 01:04:49,431
Okay. So is he counting
or is he just getting lucky?

